tools/ — vendored headers from upstream repos. Populated at Phase 0 build:

  jannus_calendar.h    — vendored from yent.aml/jannus-r/tools/
  jannus_spa.h         — vendored from yent.aml/jannus-r/tools/
  jannus_split.h       — vendored from yent.aml/jannus-r/tools/
  yent_forward.h       — vendored from yent.aml/tools/
  resonance_forward.h  — vendored from resonance.aml/tools/, with
                         Mac Accelerate flags dropped, nt_blas_matvec
                         substituted for cblas_sgemm (FIX from review)
  notorch.{c,h}        — vendored from ~/arianna/notorch/

Vendoring happens at Phase 0 on the pod, not in git (these files are
upstream artefacts). Heart.c keeps its own `.gitignore` line for
`tools/*.{h,c}` if needed, or vendors with explicit upstream-version
headers per file.
